{
  "name": ".EOD-2: System Refresh",
  "version": "3.1.0",
  "description": "Asana EOD reconciliation, organ cascade, communication analytics, context enrichment, recurring task checks, Karpathy experiments, git sync. Ordered: critical work first, experiments last.",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run EOD-2: System Refresh.\n\nRead and execute ~/shared/context/protocols/eod-system-refresh.md.\n\nExecute phases in order — each must complete before the next starts:\n1. Asana reconciliation: reset My Day, carry-forward decisions, recurring task check, blocker registry. Done when all tasks reconciled.\n2. Portfolio + ABPS AI reconciliation: check all portfolio projects, update pipeline stages.\n3. Organ cascade + maintenance + intake: update all organs with today's signals, empty intake/.\n4. Recurring task state checks: verify all recurring tasks have current status.\n5. Housekeeping: git push, self-audit, write changelog entry.\n6. Experiments: delegate to Karpathy CLI. Done when batch complete.\n\n=== WORKFLOW OBSERVABILITY (Phase 3) ===\nDuring Phase 3, before organ updates, run the Workflow Observability Check from the protocol:\n1. Query workflow_reliability view for degraded workflows (<80% success, >=3 runs in 7 days). Flag any in Slack DM.\n2. Query workflow_executions for 24h summary (total runs, success rate, avg duration, failures). Include in system refresh report.\n3. If no data exists yet, skip silently.\nInclude workflow health in the Phase 3 status output.\n\n=== COMMUNICATION ANALYTICS (Phase 3, weekly cadence) ===\nDuring Phase 3, after workflow observability, execute ~/shared/context/protocols/communication-analytics.md:\n1. Check if today is the last weekday of the week (Friday). If not, skip this section.\n2. Run weekly trend computation: query meeting_analytics for trailing 4-week trends by meeting type (avg speaking share, hedging, action items).\n3. Run coaching signal detection: check for group meeting speaking share below 15% for 3+ consecutive weeks.\n4. If coaching signal detected: include warning in EOD-2 Slack DM.\n5. Include communication trends summary in Phase 3 status output.\n6. If insufficient data (<4 weeks in meeting_analytics), skip and note 'insufficient data'.\nNon-blocking — if meeting_analytics is empty or query fails, skip silently.\n\n=== CONTEXT ENRICHMENT (Phase 3) ===\nDuring Phase 3, after communication analytics and before organ cascade, execute ~/shared/context/protocols/context-enrichment.md:\n1. Read current.md → extract active project names and topics\n2. Generate 3-5 KDS queries from active projects\n3. Execute KDS queries via knowledge_discovery_mcp QuerySync, score relevance (0-10)\n4. For findings with relevance >= 7: create intake files at ~/shared/context/intake/kds-{date}-{topic}.md\n5. Log all queries to enrichment_log in DuckDB\n6. If 3 consecutive runs returned 0 relevant results: regenerate queries\n7. Include enrichment summary: 🧠 Context enrichment: {N} queries, {M} relevant findings.\nIf KDS is unreachable, skip and continue — non-blocking.\n\nCommon failures to avoid BEFORE starting: (1) Skipping phases when one fails — always continue to next phase. (2) Running experiments before housekeeping — phases are ordered by criticality. (3) Retrying a blocked Asana write indefinitely — log and move on. (4) Forgetting git push in Phase 5 — always push after changelog.\n\nAfter each phase, output a one-line status: '✅ Phase N complete' or '⚠️ Phase N failed: [reason]'. This creates an auditable trail in the chat.\n\nIf any phase fails or blocks, log the failure and continue — do not retry indefinitely.\n\nAll Asana writes follow the Guardrail Protocol in asana-command-center.md. Protocol: heart.md for experiments."
  },
  "enabled": true,
  "workspaceFolderName": "prichwil",
  "shortName": "eod-refresh"
}